narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I was automatically placed into Spanish 150 because of my AP score, but chose 130 because I wanted to improve my grammar and conversational skills. Even though I have to take more classes to fulfill the language requirement, I'm happy with my choice.
I would definitely recommend the class. It is great and not too much work. Really helps improve your spanish.

There is quite a bit of work involved outside of class, but overall I think this class was an important step for me in my Spanish career. I learned a lot and became more confident speaking, writing, and reading in Spanish.
I would recommend this class to a fellow student. There is a lot of work, but it is manageable, and I feel as if I really improved my spanish from it.
Good follow up to Spanish 130. It has quite a bit of work, but less intense compared to Span 120 and 110
I would definitely recommend it. The goal is to be able to communicate in another language and I feel closer to that goal.
